      fix(ruby): allow instance/class variable metavars and array-pattern ellipsis
      
      Augments the Semgrep Ruby grammar to recognize two more pattern shapes that
      users hit in real rules:
      
      - LANG-485: `@$X` and `@@$X` are now valid instance / class variable
        metavars. The upstream tokens are extended with `@\$[A-Z_][A-Z_0-9]*` /
        `@@\$[A-Z_][A-Z_0-9]*` regexes (high precedence so the metavar form
        wins over `@` followed by something else).
      - LANG-491: `...` is now a valid pattern element inside array, find and
        hash patterns (e.g. `case x in [\$A, \$B, ...]`). Done by extending
        `_pattern_expr_basic` with `semgrep_ellipsis`. The expected new
        `_pattern_expr_basic` reductions overlap with `pair`, `keyword_pattern`
        and `_primary` when the body collapses to just `...`, so a few new
        conflicts entries are added; tree-sitter is happy with any of those
        reductions and the Generic translation does not care which is chosen.
      
      LANG-481 (`?` / `!` predicate-bang suffix on metavars) is intentionally
      deferred: that is a scanner / entry-point level lexer change rather than
      an additive grammar rule, and is being tracked separately.
      
